==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tenebrae
<hw>Ten"e*brae</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., pl.,
darkness.]</ety> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>The matins and lauds for
the last three days of Holy Week, commemorating the sufferings and death
of Christ, -- usually sung on the afternoon or evening of Wednesday,
Thursday, and Friday, instead of on the following days.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tenebricose</ent>⟦br⟧
